Sheffield United have bowed to the wishes of their fans and severed their relationship with convicted rapist Ched Evans.

Club officials sparked a public outcry when they accepted a request from the Professional Footballers' Association to let their former striker train with the club following his release after serving half of a five-year prison sentence.

Evans maintains he is innocent of raping a woman in a hotel room in April 2012 and has made an application to the criminal cases review commission for an appeal.

Ched Evans, pictured in Wilmslow, Cheshire on Wednesday, will not be allowed to train at his old club 

