But the announcement last week to let Evans train with the club led to several high profile supporters standing down as patrons of the club, while Olympic champions Jessica Ennis-Hill said she would want the stand named after her at Bramall Lane to be renamed if Evans was re-signed.

Television presenter Charlie Webster, musicians Paul Heaton and Dave Berry and Sheffield businesswoman Lindsay Graham have all resigned from their roles with the club, while a petition against Evans rejoining the club attracted more than 150,000 signatures.

The club board came under further pressure when Ennis-Hill's statement led to her being subjected to sickening abuse on Twitter.

Evans was released from prison in October after serving two-and-a-half years of a five-year rape sentence

